Chilean Stocks: Empresas Iansa, Empresas La Polar, Lan Airlines

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-07-29T20:42:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/chilean-stocks-empresas-iansa-empresas-la-polar-lan-airlines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:16 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.2 percent to 4,425.98.  Empresas Iansa SA (IANSA)   fell 2.4 percent to 45.11
pesos, its lowest price in three weeks.  Chile ’s largest sugar
producer reported a 16 percent decline in second-quarter profit
to $3.3 million, according to a statement posted on the website
of Chile’s securities regulator.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   rose 8.4 percent to 510.3
pesos, the biggest increase in three weeks. The Chilean retailer
that set aside $900 million last month for consumer lending
losses received approval from holders of two series of bonds to
seek a court agreement to renegotiate repayments and avoid
bankruptcy.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   fell 3.1 percent to 12,036 pesos,
the biggest fall since February.  Latin America ’s largest airline
by market value dropped the most among members of the IPSA index
as the  U.S. economy  grew less than forecast and after the
airline reported July 27 a lower-than-expected second-quarter
profit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
